tly literal to the source structure.\n\nLooking at the command-line arguments section, I notice the source has what appears to be a grammatical quirk (\"以下のである\" instead of \"以下のとおりである\"), but the knowledge file handles this fine by not reproducing that exact phrasing. The opening statement about how Nablarch interprets command-line arguments seems to be partially captured in the knowledge file, though I should verify the exact wording matches the intent.\n\nChecking the work-unit processing section, the framework's behavior of invoking the batch action's handle method for each work unit read from the reader is accurately reflected in the knowledge file, just more concisely stated.\n\nThe analysis reveals one minor gap: the knowledge file for s5 is missing the reference to `Main` from `nablarch.fw.launcher.Main`. This is the key finding worth noting in the output.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24069,"cache_read_input_tokens":29807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":24069,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e6b897f-03d7-4084-bdfc-ed174aaa3993","uuid":"ecb355f8-8757-425c-8020-e79504647026"}
